I will refine the `awk` scripts to correctly parse the JaCoCo and Clover XML reports and extract the covered lines.

For JaCoCo (`jacoco.xml`):
-   Extract `package name` from `<package name="...">`
-   Extract `sourcefilename` from `<class ... sourcefilename="...">`
-   Extract `nr` (line number) and `ci` (covered instructions) from `<line nr="..." ci="..."/>`
-   A line is considered covered if `ci > 0`.

For Clover (`clover.xml`):
-   Extract `package name` from `<package name="...">` (and convert `.` to `/`)
-   Extract `name` (filename) from `<file name="...">`
-   Extract `num` (line number) and `count` (covered statements) from `<line num="..." count="..."/>`
-   A line is considered covered if `count > 0`.

The script will then use `comm` to find unique lines in each set.

